Florian Opahle (born 1983) is a German rock musician, best known for his work with progressive rock artist Ian Anderson of band Jethro Tull, with whom he played from 2003 to 2019.
From 2017 to 2019 he was the lead guitarist of Anderson's revived version of Jethro Tull.
In 2001 and 2002, he attended master classes with Masayuki Kato, in 2002 he passed his high school diploma.

From 2007 to 2008 he studied music arrangement and composition at the German Pop Academy.
